					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052" rend="visible">
						<summary>A second volume belonging to a series of Karaite service-books, which have been originally deposited in the Karaite Synagogue in Jerusalem.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79090052">
							<locus from="1r" to="212v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">סידור </title>
							<filiation>Cf. Or 2530, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">726</ref>, for the first volume of the serie of five. </filiation>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="9r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">[Tsiduḳ ha-din]</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="9r" to="212v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Service for Yom kipur</title>
								<note>
									<p>The morning service starts on folio 9r; the afternoon service starts on folio 164r; the Ten Commandments begin on folio 173v; Ṿiduyim start on folio 174r. </p>
									<p>The hafṭarah consists of the book of Jonah and starts on folio 187v. </p>
									<p>The alphabethical pieces start on folio 193r, then follows a kind of a ne῾ilah prayer (folio 196v), and then other poetical and alphabethical pieces (folios 200v-212v).</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th to 18th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>212 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>195</height>
										<width>146</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>212 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of originally 10 leaves each. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning. </p>
									<p>Lacuna after folio 8. </p>
									<p>Many of the extant leaves are more or less damaged. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="17 22" writtenLines="17 22">
									<p>Section titles written in larger square characters. </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="4">
							<summary>Oriental square and semi-cursive script of the 16th to 17th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Previous user's entries, partially illegible: inscribed with a date of <date calendar="Hebrew">5476</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1716</date>); folio 212v. </p>
						</additions>
